analysis.info: BUSTED (branch-site unrestricted statistical test of episodic diversification) uses a random effects branch-site model fitted jointly to all or a subset of tree branches in order to test for alignment-wide evidence of episodic diversifying selection. Assuming there is evidence of positive selection (i.e. there is an omega > 1), BUSTED will also perform a quick evidence-ratio style analysis to explore which individual sites may have been subject to selection.
analysis.citation: *Gene-wide identification of episodic selection*, Mol Biol Evol. 32(5):1365-71
analysis.requirements: in-frame codon alignment and a phylogenetic tree (optionally annotated with {})
